I'll calculate the Quick Ratio and Net Profit Margin based on the financial statements provided.

## Step 1: Calculate the Quick Ratio
Quick Ratio = (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities

From the balance sheet:
- Current Assets = $9,122,854.19
- Inventory = $7,869,940.00
- Current Liabilities = $3,389,719.66

Quick Ratio = (9,122,854.19 - 7,869,940.00) / 3,389,719.66
Quick Ratio = 1,252,914.19 / 3,389,719.66
Quick Ratio = 0.3697

## Step 2: Calculate the Net Profit Margin
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%

From the income statement:
- Net Profit = $111,731.83
- Total Revenue = $791,992.51

Net Profit Margin = (111,731.83 / 791,992.51) × 100%
Net Profit Margin = 0.1411 × 100%
Net Profit Margin = 14.11%

## Final Answer
Rounded to 2 decimal places:
- Quick Ratio = 0.37
- Net Profit Margin = 14.11%
